Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 351. Page 261
Description.abstract: ff. 125-126 [Chronicle, Anno 1600]: Anno 1600 haven auch die Schreiner Ihren Tannz gehalten, ...Illustrated chronicle of the butcher guild's participation in the Fassnacht festival during the years 1449-1539, and 1600. First folios contain both verse and prose chronicle about origins of the Schempartlauf; yearly entries presented as a bifolium: text on one page and full-page illustration of costume worn that year on facing page. Ends with 5 double folios depicting various activities of the Fassnacht, including a full pageant street scene. Description for individual years includes name of leader or leaders, number of men under him, route of procession, and description of the costume. Appears to have been made as complete unit. Origin of the Schempart manuscripts as a distinct group of manuscripts is generally unknown. Certain characteristics are shared among all known extant manuscripts (about 50), and *170/351 contains all material that Sumberg and Roller cite for typical Schempart book, plus additional material, which is in the form of chronicle, mentioning events, such as wars or natural disasters, names of enemies, and distinguished visitors to the city that year, possibly unique to this manuscript. Illustrations identical in outline to most of other manuscripts, though variations occur in color and small details.
